08/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO's Supreme Allied Commander for Europe, General James L. Jones, praised Macedonia's readiness to participate in peacekeeping missions in Afghanistan and Iraq, during a meeting of Alliance officials, members of the Macedonian Defence Ministry and US Ambassador Lawrence Butler in Skopje late last week. . Participants also discussed joint projects suggested for implementation next year by the NATO advisory team in Macedonia. (A1 TV - 06/11/04)
